jdrasil.algorithms.lowerbounds

Class DegeneracyLowerbound<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • jdrasil.algorithms.lowerbounds.DegeneracyLowerbound<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T -
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.util.concurrent.Callable<java.lang.Integer>, Lowerbound<T>

    public class DegeneracyLowerbound<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>
extends java.lang.Object
implements Lowerbound<T>, java.io.Serializable
    We call a Graph G=(V,E) d-degenerated if each subgraph H of G contains a vertex of maximal degree d. It is a well known fact that we have \(d \le tw(G)\) and, thus, we can use the degeneracy of a graph as lowerbound for the tree-width. This class implements the linear time algorithm from Matula and Beck to compute the degeneracy of a graph.
